  "name": "RPlog_35_ISY_Competition_Vapor_vs_Slush",
  "title": "Vapor vs. Slush: A Duel of Generations",
  "summary": "In a TIE fighter simulator match of the 35 ISY tournament, veteran Admiral Jal'Dana, flying under the call sign Vapor, is drawn against the young cadet Liza Molokai, call sign Slush. What the watching crowd expects to be a one-sided rout becomes a tense, evenly matched dogfight, the two pilots trading hit for hit and dodge for dodge through a series of scissor loops and aggressive passes while their respective fans roar. Vapor relies on deliberate, controlled flying to dictate the pace, while Slush answers with the raw aggression and speed of youth, even resisting the temptation to taunt her opponent. In the end the Admiral's experience prevails: a heroic shot disables Liza's craft for the kill, leaving Slush at 0-3 in the competition. Far from gloating, Jal'Dana radios her respect, telling Molokai she would fly on her wing any day.",
